<seg id=1> Chinese Insurance Control Project Starts Up in Beijing </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, January 21st. Lately, a research project went underway in Beijing, which aims to assist the People's Bank of China to control the insurance regulations established by insurance organizations from China and abroad, and to press for an insurance standardization system and measures. </seg>
<seg id=3> The project, which was jointly funded by Royal and Sun Association Insurance of UK and Lincoln National Group of the US, was undertaken by PriceWaterHouse Cooper of the US, and involved a total investment amount of US$1.4 million. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> This insurance control project will systematically analyze foreign-invested insurance and existing insurance laws and regulations, and make implement a research plan that is beneficial to the development of insurance monitoring laws and regulations. </seg>
<seg id=5> The newly begun control project will deepen the research into current insurance regulations of the People's Bank of China to control foreign insurance organizations, devoting it to reinforce the management of organizational structure and operational processes, especially early warning systems. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> According to the introduction, the new insurance control regulations will perfect the current control system of foreign insurance organization in the Chinese market as well as assist the People's Bank of China in reinforcing the entire control system of the insurance market. </seg>
</p>
